-- Isramco Drops Most in Three Weeks as Investors Trade in Rights
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-07-04T13:46:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/isramco-drops-most-in-three-weeks-as-investors-trade-in-rights.html
Isramco Negev 2 LP (ISRAL)  dropped the most
in three weeks as investors traded in a rights offering today.  Shares of the Petah Tikva, Israel-based company dropped 4.2
percent to 0.456 shekel at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . The
benchmark TA-25 index slid less than 0.1 percent.  Isramco said it expects to raise as much as 130 million
shekels from the exercise of the rights offering, according to a
filing June 14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  